{
  "texts": [
    "The company also changed the rules, indicating whether the authors used AI-based tools in their products (Horlach, 2023).",
    "This situation caused outrage in the Authors Guild: more than 8,000 writers signed a collective letter to AI companies demanding decent compensation for using their copyrighted works for AI training (Knight, 2023).",
    "As a consequence, new terms \"AI-generated\" and \"AI-assisted\" have emerged (Creamer, 2023).",
    "The first one is used when the initial text is created by AI-agent, even with significant human editing afterwards.",
    "\"AI-assisted\" is used to describe works initially created by humans but refined using AI tools such as grammar and spellcheckers or even language and style analysis tools (Clark et al., 2018)."
  ]
}